# To check IP address:
  -> Use <ipconfig> in Windows terminal.
        :Under Wireless LAN adapter Wi-fi:
            - IPv4 Address =  your device IP(provided by the Wifi router)
            - Default Gateway = Wifi router's IP
        :Under VMnet8 section:
            - IPv4 Address =  Virtual Workstation's IP
  -> Use <ifconfig> in Linux(kali) terminal.
        :Under eth0:
            - inet = virtual machines(Kali)'s IP

# Path taken by virtual machine to access Internet.
    : VM(kali) -> VW(VMware) -> Device -> Router
      
